Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about automatic speech recognition (ASR) which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with acoustic data and speech signals. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper involves processing of speech signals. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel modular training framework for E2E ASR using neural models. 
- cs.SD (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method in both training and decoding.
